parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to the risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbags may not deploy properly or may explode and send shrapnel into the cabin.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available for repair
manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard near the airbag can cause the airbag to deploy improperly, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the dashboard near the airbag
concern about projectiles in the event of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy
warning lights or indicators on the dashboard
accidents or near-misses without airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor or electrical system can lead to the airbag not deploying properly, or deploying unnecessarily, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights or indicators on the dashboard
faulty airbag sensors
corrosion or moisture damage to electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard around the passenger airbag can impair the safety and design of the airbag, potentially causing it to malfunction or deploy improperly in the event of an accident, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks on the dashboard around the passenger airbag
loose feeling around the cracked area
noise from the dashboard while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incompatibility of the factory-installed brake controller with trailer braking systems using electric over hydraulic systems can cause loss of brake control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Loss of brake control
inability to stop the vehicle
near-miss accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake light system can cause the brake lights to remain on even when the brakes are not engaged, which can lead to confusion or accidents on the road.
symptoms: Brake lights staying on even when the brakes are not engaged
intermittent brake light malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle can cause the door to become stuck or unable to open, which can lead to safety issues in emergency situations.
symptoms: Broken door handle
inability to open the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the dashboard can lead to a compromised airbag system, potentially causing injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Cracks on the dashboard
particularly near the airbag area
instrument cluster
or passenger side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the door handles can lead to difficulties in entering or exiting the vehicle, potentially causing injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Door handles come off in the user's hand
rendering the door inoperable from the outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Collapse of the rear bumper can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries while towing.
symptoms: Rear bumper collapses while towing
lacks strength and towing ability as advertised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Detachment of the spare tire can cause accidents or injuries to other drivers, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Spare tire detaches from the vehicle while driving
rolls into incoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent tailgate cable lengths can cause the tailgate to malfunction, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: One cable is loose when the tailgate is lowered
not supporting the tailgate.
